-- Third Point's Loeb takes stakes in Fibra Uno, YPF, Royal DSM -letter
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Fri Jul 18, 2014 11:52AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, July 18 (Reuters) - Daniel Loeb, head of hedge fund Third Point, said in his second-quarter investor letter dated Friday that he expected market volatility to continue and still saw opportunities in Japan.

Loeb, an activist investor, cited Japan as the hedge fund's "biggest source of losses" this year. He also said his fund took a stake in Mexican REIT Fibra Uno, Argentine oil company YPF, and Royal DSM.